Long-term weather pattern in a region
Organising and summarising search results for you

Climate refers to the long-term weather pattern in a region, typically averaged over a period of 30 years. It encompasses the mean and variability of meteorological variables, such as temperature and precipitation, over time. In essence, climate is the summation of atmospheric conditions that define the environment of a particular area over extended periods. 



