How long does a region's climate last?We usually define a regionâ€™s climate over a period of 30 years. The Earthâ€™s climate system has many components. It includes everything that can affect the weather, such as the atmosphere, clouds, oceans, and the land surface and vegetation. Ice also affects our climate, through glaciers, sea ice or ice sheets on land.



